{
  "texts": [
    "Model serialization can occur any number of times so the n-ary relationship between a model program object and a model serialized object is 1:M. • Model Image is a serialized model packaged for deployment as an inference server.",
    "This packaging makes a serialized model remotely accessible and deployable.",
    "A Model Image is frequently maintained as a persistent artifact in an image server such as DockerHub.",
    "• Inference Execution Instance represents an inference server, a running executable.",
    "It is a time-bounded instance of model while executing."
  ]
}